<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>Data Collection:
The Color Picker Chrome Extension collects data solely for the purpose of enhancing user experience and functionality. This includes capturing colors from webpages and storing user preferences, such as custom color palettes.
Types of Data Collected:
The extension may collect information such as color codes, URLs of visited webpages, and user settings (e.g., custom color palettes).
Data Usage:
Collected data is used exclusively within the extension to provide its intended functionality, such as displaying captured colors and organizing custom color palettes.
Data Storage:
User data collected by the extension is stored locally on the user's device and is not transmitted to any external servers or third parties.
Data Security:
The Color Picker Chrome Extension implements appropriate security measures to protect user data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.
Data Sharing:
User data collected by the extension is not shared with any third parties, except as required by law or to comply with legal processes.
User Rights:
Users have the right to access, update, or delete their data collected by the extension. They can do so by accessing the extension's settings or contacting the developer directly.
Policy Updates:
This privacy policy may be updated periodically to reflect changes in the extension's features or to comply with legal requirements. Users will be notified of any significant changes to the privacy policy.</p>

